The evolution of gear can unlock greater effectiveness for the end-user. While skill still beats gear, it's undeniable that gear still matters a lot. node.text:
Skill > Gear. It’s something we’ve been saying for years. So when it comes to getting the latest and greatest Sidecar holster… no you don’t absolutely have to upgrade. The Legacy Sidecar still gets you from point A to B. We know that’s not going to stop you from getting that new-new, but it’s important to remember that skill still beats gear. Focus on what matters most.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #sidecar #holster

Our Rifle Basics Class is available, for free, at TREX-ARMS.com.
Advanced shooting is all about mastering fundamentals and this 3 hour video captures Lucas breaking it down for a class of students. Check it out, take notes, and make a personal plan for improvement. This release also marks the launch of our new Training page, complete with a video archive of previous training videos, printable targets, drills, weapon and gear loadouts, and more.
And we're still just getting started...
-

Taking one class a year and using it to gather homework that you can use to improve on your own time is way more valuable than taking class after class after class and never really improving that much. Over the years, we have stressed the importance of personal education followed up with hard work and consistent practice. Eventually though, we all run into the problem of plateauing and that's where classes come in.
-
This year Lucas took a private class with @Joel.Park_ of @Practicalshootingtraininggroup and collected a lot of things he can be working on, which is what you're seeing here.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

Candela is the measurement of directional light and is often a better way to determine what a flashlight is actually doing. High candela creates focused hot spots like on the @modlitesystems OKW and are very blinding and push light a really long way. When working inside though, that hot center can create a lot of shadows at whatever you are not lighting up. Options like the @surefire_llc M600 are often more flexible inside because of the "flood" of light that it throws. Though there are several great options for weapon lights on the market (Modlite, Surefire, Streamlight) finding what will work best given the environments you commonly find yourself in is crucial.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
Shoot: Find the threat, engage the threat and keep your rifle loaded. 
Move: Advance in the desired direction while staying safe.
Communicate: Keep your buddy up to date on what's going on and what you need.
-
Shooting is something we all strive to do well, moving and communicating are both done on a daily basis but can become complex when in gear and with radios. Still, they are all basic civilian tasks that should be practiced together. Keep it simple and execute cleanly.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
What you carry, is just as important as how you carry it. A backpack with medical items at the bottom of the bag isn't going to help much. Mags carried in inconsistent ways are not going to offer you much consistency in reloads. Finally, slings that snag or inhibit movement can cause just as much problem as having no sling at all. So, take time to set up your kit and find what works for you.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
Do you carry a gun that can go in an OWB holster as well? Are there upsides to concealing a smaller gun than your "duty" pistol? Are there down sides to having the same gun no matter what? We tend to look at it this way: If our gun does have to come out of our holster in a real world situation, we want every advantage possible. ⁠
-⁠

MCXs used to be a gun nobody cared about or paid attention to. You could pick them up for $1400-1800. But after Modern Warfare, some pictures of some high-speed guys, and a stream of videos from some shooters; they disappeared. They’ve even jumped to over $4k on Gunbroker. A lot of products these days simply sell because they have some “cool” factor. And sometimes that’s the missing ingredient to your product. Regardless of how good or quality your product is. Don’t disregard aesthetic, present/future culture, or trends when marketing your product.
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #mcx #sigmcx #culture #business

node.text:
Uncommon designs are often because someone doesn't know very much, or because they know a lot. Take this offset RMR for example. It's canted to the inside of the gun (for a right-handed shooter). This is usually less consistent when compared to a dot on the outside. Maybe it's here because someone hasn't experimented enough, or maybe it's because they know something you don't. If the gun is intended to only be shot while prone, maybe this works best. Maybe the glass fogs up when the ejection port spits gas. The point is this: If you see a build that looks different to you, don't assume that the person who built it is the dummy. Seek to understand before being understood. You might just learn something.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

Anyone who has shot with a flashlight knows how the debris in the air will catch and spill your light. Sure, this is training ammo and dirtier than higher-end carry ammo, but the issue applies to both. Notice in the first clip how much carbon, smoke, and crud is in front of @drewhopkins the entire time. In the second clip, he keeps moving and creates new angles between himself and the targets. As he does, he is stepping away from the visual block and buys himself better visibility. Lumens and candela are not always the answer. Sometimes movement makes all the difference. ⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

How do you learn? What process to you need in order to gather and digest information? For some, they have to read over notes. If that's the case, try taking notes before, during and after the range. For other people, they have to verbalize what they are learning. Once these people articulate their own thoughts, the concept becomes clearer. If this is how you learn, find someone who is on the same path as you and start coaching each other. Do what you can to actually learn from your range time, instead of just pulling triggers. ⁠

Being presentable in a stressful situation can go a long way. Why does the military or law enforcement have haircut and shaving standards? For one, it makes people feel like a team but also, because it causes a third party to view them in a better light. Lets break it down even farther. Lets say you need to call medical assistance and have two people show up to help. Would you rather have these people be fit, well dressed and presentable, or the exact opposite? Regardless of the job we do, presentation of ourselves can make a difference.⁠
